q4.value:
1.	Swearing will improve performance of three physical endurance tasks - namely the plank, push ups and wall sitting - relative to non-swearing;
2.	Swearing will produce increased heart rate and decreased heart rate variability while performing these tasks, relative to non-swearing;
3.	Swearing will produce increased systolic and dyostolic blood pressure while performing these tasks, relative to non-swearing;
4.	Pain ratings during the endurance tasks will be reduced in the swearing condition relative to the non-swearing condition
5.	Flow during the endurance tasks will be increased in the swearing condition relative to the non-swearing condition
6.	There will be an absence of carryover effects arising from the repeated measures analysis

